Next Steps to Compile
-- Get libretro.h: Download it from Libretro GitHub and place it in the folder.
-- Dependencies: Ensure Lua and lodepng are available to the Makefile.
-- Build: Run make in the terminal.
Test: Open RetroArch, go to Load Core, select your generated .dll or .so, then Load Content and pick a .p8 file.

Run make to build the core.